                        <h2>About me</h2>
                        <p class="lead mb-5">
							Hey, welcome to my portfolio!<br><br>

							I'm Sergio, a biomedical engineer-turned-game developer from Colombia with a passion for crafting immersive experiences. While my journey began in the world of biomedical engineering, I've since embarked on an exciting adventure in game development.<br><br>

							With an MSc (and a honor degree!) in electronic engineering, I've fine-tuned my research skills and discovered a talent for teaching. I've even published multiple scientific articles and designed innovative courses, all while teaching a variety of subjects, from signal processing to programming in languages like MATLAB, Python, and C# to development of brain-computer interfaces.<br><br>

							But what truly excites me is the creative power of programming. I've leveraged this passion to delve into assistive technologies, using machine learning to solve real-world problems. Now, I'm applying the same passion to game development, where code becomes the blueprint for crafting interactive worlds and storytelling.<br><br>

							My unique background brings a blend of analytical thinking, problem-solving, and a dash of scientific curiosity to the game industry. I'm all about creating memorable experiences, and I'd love to explore how my skills can contribute to your next gaming adventure.<br><br>

							Let's build something amazing together!

